cs.ET, cs.AR, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.ET (Embedded Systems) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on optimizing System-on-Chip (SoC) designs, which are a type of embedded system. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is also likely as the paper deals with the design and optimization of hardware systems. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possibility as the paper discusses the relationships between data in SoCs, which could be seen as a type of network. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possibility as the paper uses a probabilistic model to test the accuracy of different methods for detecting relationships in SoC data. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with optimizing SoC designs, which could involve software components.
